#. <section class="sutta" id="mn5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn5:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 5"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn5:0.2"
msgid "Anaṅgaṇasutta"
msgstr "Unblemished"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn5:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn5:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho āyasmā sāriputto bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There Sāriputta addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn5:1.4"
msgid "“āvuso bhikkhave”ti."
msgstr "“Reverends, mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn5:1.5"
msgid "“Āvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū āyasmato sāriputtassa paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Reverend,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn5:1.6"
msgid "Āyasmā sāriputto etadavoca:"
msgstr "Sāriputta said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.25"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:2.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, āvuso, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ."
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world."

msgctxt "mn5:2.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "mn5:2.3"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, ekacco puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"One person with a blemish doesn’t truly understand: ‘There is a blemish in "
"me.’"

msgctxt "mn5:2.4"
msgid ""
"Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’"
"ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"But another person with a blemish does truly understand: ‘There is a blemish "
"in me.’"

msgctxt "mn5:2.5"
msgid ""
"Idhāvuso, ekacco puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"One person without a blemish doesn’t truly understand: ‘There is no blemish "
"in me.’"

msgctxt "mn5:2.6"
msgid ""
"Idha panāvuso, ekacco puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’"
"ti yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"But another person without a blemish does truly understand: ‘There is no "
"blemish in me.’"

msgctxt "mn5:2.7"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ sāṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ "
"hīnapuriso akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"In this case, of the two persons with a blemish, the one who doesn’t "
"understand is said to be worse,"

msgctxt "mn5:2.8"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ sāṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ "
"seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyati."
msgstr "while the one who does understand is better."

msgctxt "mn5:2.9"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ anaṅgaṇānaṃyeva "
"sataṃ hīnapuriso akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"And of the two persons without a blemish, the one who doesn’t understand is "
"said to be worse,"

msgctxt "mn5:2.10"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo anaṅgaṇova samāno ‘natthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, ayaṃ imesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ anaṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ "
"seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyatī”ti."
msgstr "while the one who does understand is better.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:3.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:3.2"
msgid ""
"“Ko nu kho, āvuso sāriputta, hetu ko paccayo yenimesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ "
"sāṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ eko hīnapuriso akkhāyati, eko seṭṭhapuriso akkhāyati?"
msgstr ""
"“What is the cause, Reverend Sāriputta, what is the reason why, of the two "
"persons with a blemish, one is said to be worse and one better?"

msgctxt "mn5:3.3"
msgid ""
"Ko panāvuso sāriputta, hetu ko paccayo yenimesaṃ dvinnaṃ puggalānaṃ "
"anaṅgaṇānaṃyeva sataṃ eko hīnapuriso akkhāyati, eko seṭṭhapuriso "
"akkhāyatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"And what is the cause, what is the reason why, of the two persons without a "
"blemish, one is said to be worse and one better?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—na chandaṃ janessati na "
"vāyamissati na vīriyaṃ ārabhissati tassaṅgaṇassa pahānāya;"
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, take the case of the person who has a blemish and does not "
"understand it. You can expect that they won’t generate enthusiasm, make an "
"effort, or rouse up energy to give up that blemish."

msgctxt "mn5:4.2"
msgid "so sarāgo sadoso samoho sāṅgaṇo saṃkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati."
msgstr ""
"And they will die with greed, hate, and delusion, blemished, with a "
"corrupted mind."

msgctxt "mn5:4.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kaṃsapāti ābhatā āpaṇā vā kammārakulā vā rajena ca malena "
"ca pariyonaddhā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a bronze dish was brought from a shop or smithy covered with dirt or "
"stains."

#. VAR: pariyodapeyyuṃ → pariyodāpeyyuṃ (?)
msgctxt "mn5:4.4"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ sāmikā na ceva paribhuñjeyyuṃ na ca pariyodapeyyuṃ, rajāpathe ca naṃ "
"nikkhipeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the owners neither used it or had it cleaned, but kept it in a dirty "
"place."

msgctxt "mn5:4.5"
msgid ""
"Evañhi sā, āvuso, kaṃsapāti aparena samayena saṃkiliṭṭhatarā assa "
"malaggahitā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Over time, wouldn’t that bronze dish get even dirtier and more stained?”"

msgctxt "mn5:4.6"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.”"

msgctxt "mn5:4.7"
msgid ""
"“Evameva kho, āvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ "
"aṅgaṇan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—na chandaṃ "
"janessati na vāyamissati na vīriyaṃ ārabhissati tassaṅgaṇassa pahānāya;"
msgstr ""
"“In the same way, take the case of the person who has a blemish and does not "
"understand it. You can expect that …"

msgctxt "mn5:4.8"
msgid "so sarāgo sadoso samoho sāṅgaṇo saṃkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati."
msgstr "they will die with a corrupted mind."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.26"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, yvāyaṃ puggalo sāṅgaṇova samāno ‘atthi me ajjhattaṃ aṅgaṇan’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti, tassetaṃ pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—chandaṃ janessati vāyamissati "
"vīriyaṃ ārabhissati tassaṅgaṇassa pahānāya;"
msgstr ""
"Take the case of the person who has a blemish and does understand it. You "
"can expect that they will generate enthusiasm, make an effort, and rouse up "
"energy to give up that blemish."

msgctxt "mn5:5.2"
msgid "so arāgo adoso amoho anaṅgaṇo asaṅkiliṭṭhacitto kālaṃ karissati."
msgstr ""
"And they will die without greed, hate, and delusion, unblemished, with an "
