msgid "Yo ceva kho, āvuso, kopo yo ca appaccayo—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:18-20.9"
msgid "ubhayametaṃ aṅgaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya21"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:21.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ icchā "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant might wish:"

#. VAR: garuṃ kareyyuṃ → garukareyyuṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn5:21.2"
msgid ""
"‘aho vata mameva bhikkhū sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, na "
"aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhū sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyun’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, I hope that the monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen will honor, respect, "
"revere, and venerate me alone, not some other mendicant.’"

msgctxt "mn5:21.3"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhū sakkareyyuṃ "
"garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, na taṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhū sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ "
"kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:21.4"
msgid ""
"‘Aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhū sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, na maṃ "
"bhikkhū sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjentī’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:21.5"
msgid "iti so kupito hoti appatīto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:21.6"
msgid "Yo ceva kho, āvuso, kopo yo ca appaccayo—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:21.7"
msgid "ubhayametaṃ aṅgaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya22-24"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:22-24.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ icchā "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:22-24.2"
msgid "‘aho vata mameva bhikkhuniyo … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:22-24.3"
msgid "upāsakā … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:22-24.4"
msgid ""
"upāsikā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ "
"upāsikā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyun’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:22-24.5"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ upāsikā sakkareyyuṃ "
"garuṃ kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ, na taṃ bhikkhuṃ upāsikā sakkareyyuṃ garuṃ "
"kareyyuṃ māneyyuṃ pūjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"But it’s possible that some other mendicant is honored, respected, revered, "
"and venerated …"

msgctxt "mn5:22-24.6"
msgid ""
"‘Aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ upāsikā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjenti, na maṃ "
"upāsikā sakkaronti garuṃ karonti mānenti pūjentī’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:22-24.7"
msgid "iti so kupito hoti appatīto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:22-24.8"
msgid "Yo ceva kho, āvuso, kopo yo ca appaccayo—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:22-24.9"
msgid "ubhayametaṃ aṅgaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya25"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.30"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:25.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ icchā "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr "It’s possible that some mendicant might wish:"

#. VAR: lābhī → lābhī assaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn5:25.2"
msgid ""
"‘aho vata ahameva lābhī assaṃ paṇītānaṃ cīvarānaṃ, na añño bhikkhu lābhī "
"assa paṇītānaṃ cīvarānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I hope I get the nicest robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and "
"supplies for the sick, not some other mendicant.’"

msgctxt "mn5:25.3"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ añño bhikkhu lābhī assa paṇītānaṃ "
"cīvarānaṃ, na so bhikkhu lābhī assa paṇītānaṃ cīvarānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But it’s possible that some other mendicant gets the nicest robes, alms-"
"food, lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick …"

msgctxt "mn5:25.4"
msgid ""
"‘Añño bhikkhu lābhī paṇītānaṃ cīvarānaṃ, nāhaṃ lābhī paṇītānaṃ cīvarānan’ti—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:25.5"
msgid "iti so kupito hoti appatīto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:25.6"
msgid "Yo ceva kho, āvuso, kopo yo ca appaccayo—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:25.7"
msgid "ubhayametaṃ aṅgaṇaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya26-27"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:26-27.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ idhekaccassa bhikkhuno evaṃ icchā "
"uppajjeyya:"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: lābhī → lābhī assaṃ (bj, mr)
msgctxt "mn5:26-27.2"
msgid "‘aho vata ahameva lābhī assaṃ paṇītānaṃ piṇḍapātānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:26-27.3"
msgid "paṇītānaṃ senāsanānaṃ … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:26-27.4"
msgid ""
"paṇītānaṃ gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ, na añño bhikkhu lābhī assa "
"paṇītānaṃ gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:26-27.5"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, āvuso, vijjati yaṃ añño bhikkhu lābhī assa paṇītānaṃ "
"gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ, na so bhikkhu lābhī assa paṇītānaṃ "
"gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn5:26-27.6"
msgid ""
"‘Añño bhikkhu lābhī paṇītānaṃ gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ, nāhaṃ "
"lābhī paṇītānaṃ gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Thinking, ‘Some other mendicant has got the nicest robes, alms-food, "
"lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick’,"

msgctxt "mn5:26-27.7"
msgid "iti so kupito hoti appatīto."
msgstr "they get angry and bitter."

msgctxt "mn5:26-27.8"
msgid "Yo ceva kho, āvuso, kopo yo ca appaccayo—"
msgstr "And that anger and that bitterness"

msgctxt "mn5:26-27.9"
msgid "ubhayametaṃ aṅgaṇaṃ."
msgstr "are both blemishes."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya28"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:28.1"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ kho etaṃ, āvuso, pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ icchāvacarānaṃ adhivacanaṃ, "
"yadidaṃ aṅgaṇanti."
msgstr "‘Blemish’ is a term for these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya29"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.31"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:29.1"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, āvuso, bhikkhuno ime pāpakā akusalā icchāvacarā appahīnā "
"dissanti ceva sūyanti ca, kiñcāpi so hoti āraññiko pantasenāsano piṇḍapātiko "
"sapadānacārī paṃsukūliko lūkhacīvaradharo, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī na ceva "
"sakkaronti na garuṃ karonti na mānenti na pūjenti."
msgstr ""
"Suppose these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes are seen and heard to be not "
"given up by a mendicant. Even though they dwell in the wilderness, in remote "
"lodgings, eat only alms-food, wander indiscriminately for alms-food, wear "
"rag robes, and wear shabby robes, their spiritual companions don’t honor, "
"respect, revere, and venerate them."

msgctxt "mn5:29.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn5:29.3"
msgid ""
"Te hi tassa āyasmato pāpakā akusalā icchāvacarā appahīnā dissanti ceva "
"sūyanti ca."
msgstr ""
"It’s because these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes are seen and heard to "
"be not given up by that venerable."

msgctxt "mn5:29.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kaṃsapāti ābhatā āpaṇā vā kammārakulā vā parisuddhā "
"pariyodātā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a bronze dish was brought from a shop or smithy clean and bright."

msgctxt "mn5:29.5"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ sāmikā ahikuṇapaṃ vā kukkurakuṇapaṃ vā manussakuṇapaṃ vā racayitvā "
"aññissā kaṃsapātiyā paṭikujjitvā antarāpaṇaṃ paṭipajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then the owners were to prepare it with the carcass of a snake, a dog, or a "
"human, cover it with a bronze lid, and parade it through the market-place."

msgctxt "mn5:29.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ jano disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "When people saw it they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn5:29.7"
msgid "‘ambho, kimevidaṃ harīyati jaññajaññaṃ viyā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘My good man, what is it that you’re carrying like a precious treasure?’"

#. VAR: apāpuritvā → avāpuritvā (bj)
msgctxt "mn5:29.8"
msgid "Tamenaṃ uṭṭhahitvā apāpuritvā olokeyya."
msgstr "So they’d open up the lid for people to look inside."

#. VAR: pāṭikulyatā → pāṭikkūlatā (bj) | pāṭikkūlyatā (s2, s3) | paṭikūlatā (mr)
#. VAR: jegucchatā ca → jegucchitā ca (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn5:29.9"
msgid ""
"Tassa sahadassanena amanāpatā ca saṇṭhaheyya, pāṭikulyatā ca saṇṭhaheyya, "
"jegucchatā ca saṇṭhaheyya;"
msgstr ""
"But as soon as they saw it they were filled with loathing, revulsion, and "
"disgust."

msgctxt "mn5:29.10"
msgid "jighacchitānampi na bhottukamyatā assa, pageva suhitānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Not even those who were hungry wanted to eat it, let alone those who had "
"eaten."

msgctxt "mn5:29.11"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, āvuso, yassa kassaci bhikkhuno ime pāpakā akusalā icchāvacarā "
"appahīnā dissanti ceva sūyanti ca, kiñcāpi so hoti āraññiko pantasenāsano "
"piṇḍapātiko sapadānacārī paṃsukūliko lūkhacīvaradharo, atha kho naṃ "
"sabrahmacārī na ceva sakkaronti na garuṃ karonti na mānenti na pūjenti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes are seen and "
"heard to be not given up by a mendicant … their spiritual companions don’t "
"honor, respect, revere, and venerate them."

msgctxt "mn5:29.12"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn5:29.13"
msgid ""
"Te hi tassa āyasmato pāpakā akusalā icchāvacarā appahīnā dissanti ceva "
"sūyanti ca."
msgstr ""
"It’s because these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes are seen and heard to "
"be not given up by that venerable."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya30"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:30.1"
msgid ""
"Yassa kassaci, āvuso, bhikkhuno ime pāpakā akusalā icchāvacarā pahīnā "
"dissanti ceva sūyanti ca, kiñcāpi so hoti gāmantavihārī nemantaniko "
"gahapaticīvaradharo, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī sakkaronti garuṃ karonti "
"mānenti pūjenti."
msgstr ""
"Suppose these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes are seen and heard to be "
"given up by a mendicant. Even though they dwell in the neighborhood of a "
"village, accept invitations to a meal, and wear robes offered by "
"householders, their spiritual companions honor, respect, revere, and "
"venerate them."

msgctxt "mn5:30.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn5:30.3"
msgid ""
"Te hi tassa āyasmato pāpakā akusalā icchāvacarā pahīnā dissanti ceva sūyanti "
"ca."
msgstr ""
"It’s because these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes are seen and heard to "
"be given up by that venerable."

msgctxt "mn5:30.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, kaṃsapāti ābhatā āpaṇā vā kammārakulā vā parisuddhā "
"pariyodātā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose a bronze dish was brought from a shop or smithy clean and bright."

#. VAR: vicitakāḷakaṃ → vicini­ta­kāḷakaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn5:30.5"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ sāmikā sālīnaṃ odanaṃ vicitakāḷakaṃ anekasūpaṃ anekabyañjanaṃ "
"racayitvā aññissā kaṃsapātiyā paṭikujjitvā antarāpaṇaṃ paṭipajjeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then the owners were to prepare it with boiled fine rice with the dark "
"grains picked out and served with many soups and sauces, cover it with a "
"bronze lid, and parade it through the market-place."

msgctxt "mn5:30.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ jano disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "When people saw it they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn5:30.7"
msgid "‘ambho, kimevidaṃ harīyati jaññajaññaṃ viyā’ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘My good man, what is it that you’re carrying like a precious treasure?’"

msgctxt "mn5:30.8"
msgid "Tamenaṃ uṭṭhahitvā apāpuritvā olokeyya."
msgstr "So they’d open up the lid for people to look inside."

msgctxt "mn5:30.9"
msgid ""
"Tassa saha dassanena manāpatā ca saṇṭhaheyya, appāṭikulyatā ca saṇṭhaheyya, "
"ajegucchatā ca saṇṭhaheyya;"
msgstr ""
"And as soon as they saw it they were filled with liking, attraction, and "
"relish."

msgctxt "mn5:30.10"
msgid "suhitānampi bhottukamyatā assa, pageva jighacchitānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Even those who had eaten wanted to eat it, let alone those who were hungry."

msgctxt "mn5:30.11"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, āvuso, yassa kassaci bhikkhuno ime pāpakā akusalā icchāvacarā "
"pahīnā dissanti ceva sūyanti ca, kiñcāpi so hoti gāmantavihārī nemantaniko "
"gahapaticīvaradharo, atha kho naṃ sabrahmacārī sakkaronti garuṃ karonti "
"mānenti pūjenti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes are seen and "
"heard to be given up by a mendicant … their spiritual companions honor, "
"respect, revere, and venerate them."

msgctxt "mn5:30.12"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn5:30.13"
msgid ""
"Te hi tassa āyasmato pāpakā akusalā icchāvacarā pahīnā dissanti ceva sūyanti "
"cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"It’s because these spheres of bad, unskillful wishes are seen and heard to "
"be given up by that venerable.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya31"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.32"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:31.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā mahāmoggallāno āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna said to him:"

msgctxt "mn5:31.2"
msgid "“upamā maṃ, āvuso sāriputta, paṭibhātī”ti."
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, a simile springs to mind.”"

msgctxt "mn5:31.3"
msgid "“Paṭibhātu taṃ, āvuso moggallānā”ti."
msgstr "“Then speak as you feel inspired,” said Sāriputta."

msgctxt "mn5:31.4"
msgid "“Ekamidāhaṃ, āvuso, samayaṃ rājagahe viharāmi giribbaje."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend, at one time I was staying right here in Rājagaha, the Mountain "
"Keep."

msgctxt "mn5:31.5"
msgid ""
"Atha khvāhaṃ, āvuso, pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya rājagahaṃ "
"piṇḍāya pāvisiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then I robed up in the morning and, taking my bowl and robe, entered "
"Rājagaha for alms."

msgctxt "mn5:31.6"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena samīti yānakāraputto rathassa nemiṃ tacchati."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Samīti the cartwright was planing the rim of a chariot "
"wheel."

# BB’s “son of a former cartwright” is implausible. Surely the point is that he used to be a cartwright. The idiom -putta is often disserved by rendering it as “son”; here it just means that he is “one of the cartwrights”, or “from a family of cartwrights”.
msgctxt "mn5:31.7"
msgid "Tamenaṃ paṇḍuputto ājīvako purāṇayānakāraputto paccupaṭṭhito hoti."
msgstr ""
"The <i>Ājīvaka</i> ascetic Paṇḍuputta, who used to be a cartwright, was "
"standing by,"

msgctxt "mn5:31.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, āvuso, paṇḍuputtassa ājīvakassa purāṇayānakāraputtassa evaṃ cetaso "
"parivitakko udapādi:"
msgstr "and this thought came to his mind:"

# suddhā assa sāre patiṭṭhitā recurs at AN 4.190 (of an assembly) and AN 3.93 (of seeds and monks). In both cases BB has “pure, established in the core”, whereas here he has “come to consist purely of heartwood”.
#. VAR: suddhā assa → suddhāssa (bj, pts1) | suddhā (mr)
msgctxt "mn5:31.9"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāyaṃ samīti yānakāraputto imissā nemiyā imañca vaṅkaṃ imañca jimhaṃ "
"imañca dosaṃ taccheyya, evāyaṃ nemi apagatavaṅkā apagatajimhā apagatadosā "
"suddhā assa sāre patiṭṭhitā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Oh, I hope Samīti the cartwright planes out the crooks, bends, and flaws in "
"this rim. Then the rim will be rid of crooks, bends, and flaws, and consist "
"purely of the essential core.’"

msgctxt "mn5:31.10"
msgid ""
"Yathā yathā kho, āvuso, paṇḍuputtassa ājīvakassa purāṇayānakāraputtassa "
"cetaso parivitakko hoti tathā tathā samīti yānakāraputto tassā nemiyā tañca "
"vaṅkaṃ tañca jimhaṃ tañca dosaṃ tacchati."
msgstr "And Samīti planed out the flaws in the rim just as Paṇḍuputta thought."

msgctxt "mn5:31.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, āvuso, paṇḍuputto ājīvako purāṇayānakāraputto attamano "
"attamanavācaṃ nicchāresi:"
msgstr "Then Paṇḍuputta expressed his gladness:"

msgctxt "mn5:31.12"
msgid "‘hadayā hadayaṃ maññe aññāya tacchatī’ti."
msgstr "‘He planes like he knows my heart with his heart!’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya32"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
#. VAR: ketabino → keṭubhino (bahūsu)
msgctxt "mn5:32.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, āvuso, ye te puggalā assaddhā, jīvikatthā na saddhā agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, saṭhā māyāvino ketabino uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā "
"vikiṇṇavācā, indriyesu aguttadvārā, bhojane amattaññuno, jāgariyaṃ "
"ananuyuttā, sāmaññe anapekkhavanto, sikkhāya na tibbagāravā, bāhulikā "
"sāthalikā, okkamane pubbaṅgamā, paviveke nikkhittadhurā, kusītā hīnavīriyā "
"muṭṭhassatī asampajānā asamāhitā vibbhantacittā duppaññā eḷamūgā, tesaṃ "
"āyasmā sāriputto iminā dhammapariyāyena hadayā hadayaṃ maññe aññāya tacchati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are those faithless people who went forth from the "
"lay life to homelessness not out of faith but to earn a livelihood. They’re "
"devious, deceitful, and sneaky. They’re restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, "
"and loose-tongued. They do not guard their sense doors or eat in moderation, "
"and they are not dedicated to wakefulness. They don’t care about the ascetic "
"life, and don’t keenly respect the training. They’re indulgent and slack, "
"leaders in backsliding, neglecting seclusion, lazy, and lacking energy. They’"
"re unmindful, lacking situational awareness and immersion, with straying "
"minds, witless and stupid. Venerable Sāriputta planes their faults with this "
"exposition of the teaching as if he knows my heart with his heart!"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:32.2"
msgid ""
"Ye pana te kulaputtā saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, asaṭhā amāyāvino "
"aketabino anuddhatā anunnaḷā acapalā amukharā avikiṇṇavācā, indriyesu "
"guttadvārā, bhojane mattaññuno, jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā, sāmaññe apekkhavanto, "
"sikkhāya tibbagāravā, na bāhulikā na sāthalikā, okkamane nikkhittadhurā, "
"paviveke pubbaṅgamā, āraddhavīriyā pahitattā upaṭṭhitassatī sampajānā "
"samāhitā ekaggacittā paññavanto aneḷamūgā, te āyasmato sāriputtassa imaṃ "
"dhammapariyāyaṃ sutvā pivanti maññe, ghasanti maññe vacasā ceva manasā ca:"
msgstr ""
"But there are those people from good families who went forth from the lay "
"life to homelessness out of faith. They’re not devious, deceitful, and "
"sneaky. They’re not restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, and loose-tongued. "
"They guard their sense doors and eat in moderation, and they are dedicated "
"to wakefulness. They care about the ascetic life, and keenly respect the "
"training. They’re not indulgent or slack, nor are they leaders in "
"backsliding, neglecting seclusion. They’re energetic and determined. They’re "
"mindful, with situational awareness, immersion, and unified minds; wise, not "
"stupid. Hearing this exposition of the teaching from Venerable Sāriputta, "
"they drink it up and devour it, as it were. And in speech and thought they "
"say:"

# BB follows PTS edition here, but MS is preferable. PTS omits the close -ti, and hence treats this sentence as a simple continuation of Moggallana’s speech. But it reads much better as an exclamation by the good monks.
msgctxt "mn5:32.3"
msgid ""
"‘sādhu vata, bho, sabrahmacārī akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s good, sirs, that he draws his spiritual companions away from the "
"unskillful and establishes them in the skillful.’"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya33"></a>
msgctxt "mn5:33.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, āvuso, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanakajātiko sīsaṃnhāto "
"uppalamālaṃ vā vassikamālaṃ vā atimuttakamālaṃ vā labhitvā ubhohi hatthehi "
"paṭiggahetvā uttamaṅge sirasmiṃ patiṭṭhapeyya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of "
"adornments, and had bathed their head. After getting a garland of lotuses, "
"jasmine, or liana flowers, they would take them in both hands and place them "
"on the crown of the head."

msgctxt "mn5:33.2"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, āvuso, ye te kulaputtā saddhā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitā, "
"asaṭhā amāyāvino aketabino anuddhatā anunnaḷā acapalā amukharā avikiṇṇavācā, "
"indriyesu guttadvārā, bhojane mattaññuno, jāgariyaṃ anuyuttā, sāmaññe "
"apekkhavanto, sikkhāya tibbagāravā, na bāhulikā na sāthalikā, okkamane "
"nikkhittadhurā, paviveke pubbaṅgamā, āraddhavīriyā pahitattā upaṭṭhitassatī "
"sampajānā samāhitā ekaggacittā paññavanto aneḷamūgā, te āyasmato "
"sāriputtassa imaṃ dhammapariyāyaṃ sutvā pivanti maññe, ghasanti maññe vacasā "
"ceva manasā ca:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, those people from good families who went forth from the lay "
"life to homelessness out of faith … say:"

msgctxt "mn5:33.3"
msgid ""
"‘sādhu vata, bho, sabrahmacārī akusalā vuṭṭhāpetvā kusale patiṭṭhāpetī’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s good, sirs, that he draws his spiritual companions away from the "
"unskillful and establishes them in the skillful.’”"

msgctxt "mn5:33.4"
msgid "Itiha te ubho mahānāgā aññamaññassa subhāsitaṃ samanumodiṃsūti."
msgstr "And so these two spiritual giants agreed with each others’ fine words."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn5:33.5"
msgid "Anaṅgaṇasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
